Distant Worlds Universe REFRESHED EM Version (DWUR-EM)

/========== About ==========\
Now that Distant Worlds Universe Refreshed is several years old, I am looking to revisit some of the assets and features. This new version of DWUR leans into the expanded capabilities of DWU from Alvek's Expansion Mod. Enjoy!
-- Salemonz

v0.9.5 -- 18 March 2026 -- Refreshed all 194 components. New images (many pulled from my DW2 mods)
v0.9.4 -- 16 March 2026 -- Refreshed flags. 75 new empire flags. 75 new pirate flags.
v0.9.3 -- 15 March 2026 -- Balance pass incorporated. 2K files edited/changed. Race stats, AI policies, design templates, pirate behavior...even dialog during diplomacy have all been refreshed. 46 races in DWUR should all behave and play very differently.
v0.9.2 -- 14 March 2026 -- Updated pirate portraits (included legendary option for EM)
v0.9.1 -- 12 March 2026 -- Updated engine exhaust graphics
v0.9.0 -- 04 March 2026 -- Initial beta release

/========== What's New ==========\
- Major balance pass completed. All 46 races now have disctinct AI behaviors, ship templates, stat adjustments and diplomatic dialog.
- Fixed the "overshadow" problem with planets and shadow textures being too large
- Added the new facility "Diplomatic Center" to the game (per ExpansionMod). Diplomatic Center increases the chance for ambassadors to spawn in empire.
- Re-worked many race portraits (25 races)...some to bring them in line with Distant Worlds 2 art direction...some because I wanted to.
- Re-worked hyperdeny graphic for better visability
- Re-worked some UI elements (character icons, mainly) for better visibility

/========== Installation ==========\
1. Download and install Alvek's Expansion Mod (EM) via his Github here: https://github.com/DW-UX/DistantWorldsExpanded. Please pay attention to the instructions (especially the need to unblock the .zip before opening) to correctly install EM.
2. Download DWUR from https://github.com/salemonz/DWUR-EM.
3. Go to your Distant Worlds: Universe game folder. Then the \CUSTOMIZATION directory.
4. Create a directory for the mod within the CUSTOMIZATION directory...you can call this whatever you'd like. This will be where you expand the mod's files.
5. Unpack the downloaded DWUR archive into the directory you created in step 4.
6. Launch the game.
7. Go to "Change Theme"
8. Pick the name of the directory you created in step 3 and click Activate Theme.
(The game might hang for up to a minute while everything loads)
9. Exit the game and restart (even though the game loads the files after clicking "Activate Theme", it only partially loads...I don't know why DW:U is like this...I'm not a developer :D You need to exit the game and restart after activating the theme.)
10. You'll know the mod is fully activated by seeing the custom DWUR background.
11. Enjoy!

/========== How to restore "Vanilla" balance ==========\
DWUR-EM has implemented a comprehensive balance pass across all 46 races. Policies, race stats, component access, ship templates, even dialog has all been edited and/or changed to make every race in DWUR feel distinct.

If you do NOT like these changes, you can restore the "vanilla" balance of old versions of DWUR.

1. Go to the \Docs folder within the mod files.
2. Open the "DWUR RESTORE VANILLA BALANCE" archive file.
3. Save the included files into your mod base folder (not the game folder...your mod folder). Overwrite when asked.